        { segment: "Large IPC Firms — India and GCC", demographics: "JLL, CBRE, Knight Frank, Anarock, and regional equivalents. 100-2,000 associate brokers. Multi-developer, multi-city relationships. Both India and GCC geographies.", industry: "Real Estate Brokerage and Advisory", painPoints: "1. (Industry) IPC firms managing hundreds of associates need consolidated performance visibility that no single developer portal provides. 2. (Company) Brokerage reconciliation across multiple developers is manual.", notSolved: "Associate productivity is unmeasurable at the firm level, brokerage leakage from unregistered sub-CPs is undetected, and IPC firms cannot demonstrate ROI to developer clients with data.", goodEnough: "Proprietary internal CRM or ERP, separate logins for each developer portal, manual Excel reconciliation of brokerage across developers." },
        { segment: "Developer Sales Heads and CP Ops Teams — India and GCC", demographics: "VP Sales, Head of CP Operations, Senior Manager CP Relations. 30-50 years old. KPIs tied to CP activation, bookings from CP channel, and brokerage payable accuracy.", industry: "Residential Real Estate (Internal Buyer)", painPoints: "1. (Industry) Channel management best practices are poorly codified in Indian real estate — most teams operate by instinct. 2. (Company) CP ops teams spend disproportionate time on administrative tasks.", notSolved: "Channel mis-management leads to booking shortfalls, high-performing CPs exit to competitors, finance team faces end-of-quarter brokerage reconciliation crunches.", goodEnough: "SFDC dashboards with manual inputs, weekly team calls for status updates, Excel-based brokerage reconciliation reviewed at month end." }
