        { category: "The One Competitor to Displace Most Aggressively", description: "Propacity. They occupy the same mid-market positioning in India, are known to the same buyers, and are the most common alternative in RFPs. Displacement strategy: lead with live SAP integration, loyalty engine, and redemption store in every demo. Propacity cannot match these on product. Request side-by-side evaluation where possible." },
        { category: "What to Stop Doing or Saying", description: "Stop describing the product as a 'CP portal.' It undersells the loyalty engine, wallet, and integration depth. Stop leading with feature lists in sales conversations — lead with the two pains that land hardest: 'your CPs don't know where their invoice is' and 'your top CPs are splitting their inventory with three developers.' These are the entry points." },
        { category: "Recommended GTM Motion — Year 1", description: "Direct enterprise sales (primary). Target VP Channel Sales and Head of CP Operations at Tier A developers. Sales cycle 3–6 months. Supplement with reference-based selling — Rustomjee and Runwal as live references at every pitch. Secondary: developer events and PropTech conferences in Mumbai and Dubai for GCC pipeline. PLG is not appropriate at this stage — the product requires onboarding support and integration work." }
